In helm with Terror's plumed crest , In adamantine steel bedight , Glistening formidably bright , With step unfixed and aspect wild ; Jealous Juno's raging child , Who thee conceived in Flora's bower , By touch of rare Olenian flower : Oft the goddess sighed in vain , Envying Jove's prolific brain , And oft she strayed Olympus round , Till this specific help she found ; Then fruitful grown , she quits the skies , To Thracia's sanguine plain she hies , There teems thee forth , of nervous mould , Haughty , furious , swift and bold , Names thee Mars , and bids thee call The world from Pleasure's flowery thrall
